house Barrowville in 1858 and 1859 from brick fired in his own yard, adapting a design from Andrew Jackson Downing's pattern book. He kept detailed records of his plantation's agriculture and weather.","number":3},{"category":"military","header":"Sherman's army camped around his house","body":"During Sherman's March to the Sea, Barrowville was made the headquarters of a Federal encampment, with thousands of soldiers camped around it. The house narrowly escaped burning when the last troops marched away.","number":4}],"slug":"william-mckinley-1809"},"H01842":{"id":"H01842","is_placeholder":false,"gender":"female","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":7,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1815,"month":4,"day":27,"city":"New Britain","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1888,"month":6,"day":1},"parents":{"father_id":"X01972","mother_id":"H00699"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X01988","date_year":1842,"date_month":8,"date_day":24,"location_city":"Berlin","location_state":"Connecticut","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1845,"children_ids":["HD2905"]},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"X01989","date_year":1848,"date_month":10,"date_day":26,"location_city":"Berlin","location_state":"Connecticut","children_ids":["HD5910","HD5911","HD5912"]}],"number_of_marriages":2,"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Cowles Genealogy"},{"bib_id":"BIB003"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"former_ids":["HD2884"],"bio":{"display_name":"Lucy Anne Andrews McKinley","first_name":"Lucy Anne","last_name":"McKinley","maiden_name":"Andrews","married_names":["Sims","McKinley"]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"lucy-anne-mckinley-1815"},"X01972":{"id":"X01972","is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":true},"birth":{"year":1787,"month":4,"day":7,"city":"New Britain","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1858,"month":3,"day":4,"city":"New Britain","state":"Connecticut"},"parents":{"father_research_notes":"Ensign Levi Andrews of Newington/New Britain CT","mother_research_notes":"Chloe, dau. of Robert Welles of Newington"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00699","children_ids":["H01840","H01841","H01842","H01843","H01844","H01845","H01846","H01847","H01848","H01849"],"date_year":1810,"date_month":12,"date_day":19,"location_city":"Farmington","location_state":"Connecticut"}],"number_of_marriages":1,"tags":["yale_connection","yale_graduate","author","academic","abolitionist","lawyer","politician"],"sources":[{"short":"Cowles Genealogy #644"},{"short":"Andrews, Hooker and Tuttle Genealogies"},{"short":"Camp's History of New Britain CT"},{"bib_id":"BIB003"}],"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["education","literature","law","social_reform"],"notable_blurb":"Latin lexicographer behind Harper's Latin Dictionary","primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethan_Allen_Andrews_(lexicographer)","primary_url_label":"Wikipedia"},"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"literature","header":"His Latin dictionary became Harper's Latin Dictionary","body":"Andrews published a Latin-English lexicon in 1850 that was revised into Harper's Latin Dictionary, a standard reference well into the twentieth century. Yale awarded him a doctorate in 1848 for his classical scholarship.","number":1},{"category":"education","header":"He taught ancient languages across the country","body":"A Yale graduate of 1810, Andrews practiced law before turning to teaching, holding a professorship of ancient languages at the University of North Carolina and later running schools in New Haven and Boston. He co-wrote a widely used Latin grammar.","number":2},{"category":"law","header":"He sat as legislator, magistrate, and judge","body":"Back in New Britain, Andrews served as a Whig state legislator, a magistrate, and a judge of probate. He kept at his books to the end, dying in 1858 in the midst of his literary labors.","number":3},{"category":"social_reform","header":"His book on slavery drew abolitionist fire","body":"In 1836 Andrews published a study of slavery and the domestic slave trade that The Liberator attacked as a pro-slavery apologia. The work set the scholar awkwardly against the rising antislavery tide of his native Connecticut.","number":4}],"cross_connections":[],"education":[{"institution_id":"INST022","school_name":"Yale College","type":"university","degree":"B.A.","graduation_year":1810,"notable":true,"institution_blurb":"Graduated Yale 1810; Yale conferred LL.D. 1848 for Latin scholarship."},{"institution_id":"INST022","school_name":"Yale University","type":"university","degree":"LL.D.","graduation_year":1848,"notable":true,"institution_blurb":"Yale conferred LL.D. 1848 for eminence as Latin author."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Prof. Ethan Allen Andrews","first_name":"Ethan","middle_name":"Allen","last_name":"Andrews","title":"Prof.","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780773321/Ethan_Allen_Andrews__page_333_crop_vj8csf.jpg"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","relationship":"alumnus"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"ethan-andrews-1787"},"H00699":{"id":"H00699","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent